1
00:00:01,345 --> 00:00:03,272
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:22,951 --> 00:01:28,839
REVIVAL

3
00:01:32,593 --> 00:01:34,803
Ryuzaki, please,
let me go and make the arrest.

4
00:01:35,072 --> 00:01:37,097
I'd like to come with you, Chief,
if that's all right.

5
00:01:37,889 --> 00:01:40,434
I understand, but remember this is Kira.

6
00:01:40,559 --> 00:01:42,728
Be sure to take every precaution
when you approach him,

7
00:01:42,853 --> 00:01:44,563
and don't allow him to see your face.

8
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:48,567
Watari, if Higuchi tries anything
or makes any sudden moves…

9
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:52,029
[Watari] Understood. I will shoot
to stop him, not to kill.

10
00:01:59,620 --> 00:02:02,831
Aizawa, do you have a helmet
or something to hide your face with?

11
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:03,832
I do.

12
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:06,168
Good. Then cover me.

13
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:09,713
Yes, sir. You can count on me, Chief.

14
00:02:10,464 --> 00:02:12,257
[quick footsteps]

15
00:02:13,342 --> 00:02:15,302
[Yagami] Higuchi, put your hands
above your head

16
00:02:15,510 --> 00:02:16,678
and get out of the car.

17
00:02:29,733 --> 00:02:31,026
[Yagami] We've apprehended him.

18
00:02:31,735 --> 00:02:34,863
Mogi, I want you to put a headset on him
as planned.

19
00:02:35,113 --> 00:02:36,198
[Mogi] Roger.

20
00:02:37,908 --> 00:02:38,992
[L] Higuchi,

21
00:02:39,076 --> 00:02:40,619
how are you able to kill people?

22
00:02:40,744 --> 00:02:42,037
Tell me!

23
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:44,414
[grunts]

24
00:02:44,748 --> 00:02:46,833
If you're not going to talk,

25
00:02:46,958 --> 00:02:49,419
I'll use whatever means necessary
to get it out of you.

26
00:02:51,588 --> 00:02:52,631
[sighs]

27
00:02:54,216 --> 00:02:55,509
The notebook.

28
00:02:55,926 --> 00:02:57,135
[L] Notebook?

29
00:02:57,219 --> 00:02:58,720
You probably won't believe me,

30
00:02:58,804 --> 00:03:00,305
but I've got a special notebook.

31
00:03:00,389 --> 00:03:02,849
If I write someone's name in it
while thinking of their face,

32
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:04,518
that person dies.

33
00:03:05,602 --> 00:03:06,812
A notebook…

34
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:08,230
Mr. Yagami.

35
00:03:08,355 --> 00:03:09,648
[Yagami] Yeah, I found it.

36
00:03:09,731 --> 00:03:12,234
It was in one of the compartments
of Higuchi's bag.

37
00:03:12,651 --> 00:03:14,403
He has written a lot of names in it,

38
00:03:14,486 --> 00:03:17,030
but there doesn't seem to be
anything else unusual about it. Huh?

39
00:03:17,989 --> 00:03:20,200
[Yagami screams]

40
00:03:20,742 --> 00:03:22,077
[L] What is it, Mr. Yagami?

41
00:03:22,786 --> 00:03:24,413
[Yagami] It's a monster!

42
00:03:24,621 --> 00:03:25,747
[L] Please calm down.

43
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:27,082
Don't panic; remember,

44
00:03:27,207 --> 00:03:29,084
you're not really armed
to defend yourself.

45
00:03:29,376 --> 00:03:31,294
Oh… oh right, of course.

46
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:33,672
[Mogi] Chief, hang in there.
Are you all right?

47
00:03:34,172 --> 00:03:36,591
Mogi, can't you see that thing over there?

48
00:03:36,842 --> 00:03:38,844
Chief, I think you must be getting tired.

49
00:03:39,428 --> 00:03:40,679
[Yagami screaming]

50
00:03:41,054 --> 00:03:42,222
Mogi, what's wrong?

51
00:03:42,597 --> 00:03:44,808
[Yagami] That… that thing.

52
00:03:44,891 --> 00:03:48,478
It seems that only people
who have touched the notebook can…

53
00:03:48,687 --> 00:03:50,981
can see this… this monster.

54
00:03:54,192 --> 00:03:56,528
[L] Please bring the notebook
over to the helicopter.

55
00:03:56,695 --> 00:03:57,946
[Yagami] Uh… o-okay.

56
00:04:01,199 --> 00:04:04,327
What in the world are you planning to do,
Light Yagami?

57
00:04:04,745 --> 00:04:06,997
Once you take hold of that notebook again,

58
00:04:07,205 --> 00:04:10,500
all the memories of the Death Note
and what you did when it was yours

59
00:04:10,584 --> 00:04:12,127
will return at once.

60
00:04:13,336 --> 00:04:14,463
However…

61
00:04:16,214 --> 00:04:17,591
[Mogi] Here it is, Ryuzaki.

62
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:21,094
Hmm...

63
00:04:26,641 --> 00:04:29,686
It really is… a Shinigami.

64
00:04:30,103 --> 00:04:33,440
They really… do… exist.

65
00:04:33,815 --> 00:04:35,066
[L] Light Yagami…

66
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:37,736
This is how Kira killed.
No, the second Kira.

67
00:04:38,153 --> 00:04:39,571
[L's thoughts echoing]

68
00:04:39,696 --> 00:04:41,323
Ryuzaki, come on, let me see it!

69
00:04:41,615 --> 00:04:43,033
[L] The Second Kira…

70
00:04:43,158 --> 00:04:44,659
Two books!

71
00:04:44,743 --> 00:04:46,328
There have to be two notebooks.

72
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:47,579
Possibly more.

73
00:04:48,205 --> 00:04:49,331
This isn't over yet.

74
00:04:58,548 --> 00:05:00,467
[Light screaming]

75
00:05:00,842 --> 00:05:04,888
[echoing voices and sounds]

76
00:05:14,648 --> 00:05:16,817
[Light panting]

77
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:21,446
Um... Are you okay, Light?

78
00:05:21,947 --> 00:05:24,324
I suppose seeing that monster
would surprise anyone.

79
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:26,701
[Light] Ryuzaki…

80
00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:28,036
What is it?

81
00:05:28,537 --> 00:05:29,746
[Light] I wanna check this out.

82
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:32,165
I'm going to try comparing the names
written in this notebook

83
00:05:32,249 --> 00:05:33,458
with the names of the victims.

84
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,585
Hmm? Oh, right.

85
00:05:36,086 --> 00:05:37,879
Yeah, that sounds like a good idea.

86
00:05:43,718 --> 00:05:45,178
I've won.

87
00:05:47,639 --> 00:05:49,140
Exactly as planned.

88
00:05:56,356 --> 00:05:59,150
I hereby forfeit
ownership of this notebook.

89
00:06:00,110 --> 00:06:03,947
Now, that means ownership
has transferred back to you, right?

90
00:06:04,114 --> 00:06:06,032
[Rem] Yes, I already told you.

91
00:06:06,825 --> 00:06:08,910
[Light] Next, pass it on to Ryuk.

92
00:06:09,327 --> 00:06:10,370
Hm?

93
00:06:11,037 --> 00:06:13,123
[sighs] Very well. Here.

94
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:18,420
Now that notebook's ownership
has transferred from you to Ryuk.

95
00:06:18,879 --> 00:06:20,589
Okay, Ryuk, take the notebook

96
00:06:20,672 --> 00:06:23,133
and drop it on the ground,
so it's in the human world again.

97
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:24,551
Huh?

98
00:06:25,135 --> 00:06:26,177
Well, okay.

99
00:06:30,307 --> 00:06:32,434
Now the ownership goes back to me.

100
00:06:32,601 --> 00:06:35,145
Wow, hang on!
It’s just gone around in a circle!

101
00:06:35,228 --> 00:06:36,980
Nothing's changed, right?

102
00:06:37,272 --> 00:06:38,940
Maybe at first glance,

103
00:06:39,816 --> 00:06:42,444
but there will be a time
when I'll benefit from this.

104
00:06:42,736 --> 00:06:45,780
Now, as for this notebook,
the one I first received,

105
00:06:46,573 --> 00:06:48,450
I’m gonna give it back to you, Ryuk.

106
00:06:48,617 --> 00:06:49,951
Then you hand it over to Rem.

107
00:06:51,161 --> 00:06:52,245
[Ryuk] Huh?

108
00:06:55,206 --> 00:06:56,207
[Ryuk] Here.

109
00:07:00,837 --> 00:07:03,673
Rem, I want you to give the notebook
to someone with status

110
00:07:03,757 --> 00:07:05,425
who lusts for power and money.

111
00:07:05,508 --> 00:07:08,136
They'll end up using the notebook
to satisfy that urge.

112
00:07:10,639 --> 00:07:11,681
If you do that,

113
00:07:11,806 --> 00:07:14,851
I can guarantee that Misa will be
released from her confinement soon.

114
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:17,812
And if I'm wrong, and it looks like
she won’t be released for years,

115
00:07:17,938 --> 00:07:18,980
then you can kill me.

116
00:07:19,064 --> 00:07:20,190
Does that sound fair to you?

117
00:07:21,232 --> 00:07:24,110
Light Yagami, just what are you thinking?

118
00:07:24,319 --> 00:07:26,446
Look, this is all to save Misa.

119
00:07:26,571 --> 00:07:28,114
You're gonna have to trust me on this.

120
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:33,119
All right.

121
00:07:33,453 --> 00:07:36,706
If it means that Misa will be saved,
I'll do as you ask.

122
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:42,379
[Light] After this, I'll go and demand
to be confined like Misa,

123
00:07:42,504 --> 00:07:45,507
and have them put me
under 24-hour surveillance as well.

124
00:07:46,007 --> 00:07:47,008
While I'm locked up,

125
00:07:47,092 --> 00:07:49,386
I'll relinquish ownership of the notebook
to you.

126
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:52,722
That'll mean I'll lose
all my memories of the Death Note.

127
00:07:53,348 --> 00:07:56,017
During this time the killings of criminals
will start again.

128
00:07:56,970 --> 00:07:58,019
KIRA RETURNS

129
00:07:58,186 --> 00:07:59,145
Once that happens,

130
00:07:59,229 --> 00:08:02,023
Ryuzaki will be put in a position
where he has to release us.

131
00:08:03,817 --> 00:08:06,319
And, after I've lost all my memories,

132
00:08:06,444 --> 00:08:08,905
chances are
I'll wanna help catch Kira myself.

133
00:08:09,906 --> 00:08:11,866
That's just the way I am.

134
00:08:12,993 --> 00:08:16,246
So, then you'll try and catch the guy
who Rem gives the notebook to

135
00:08:16,413 --> 00:08:18,331
and steal it before L gets to it!

136
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:19,457
[Light] Right.

137
00:08:19,582 --> 00:08:22,711
Once that's done,
I'll kill the new owner of the notebook.

138
00:08:23,378 --> 00:08:25,922
But there's still one problem remaining.

139
00:08:26,297 --> 00:08:27,924
[Rem] If you don't have full ownership,

140
00:08:28,091 --> 00:08:31,636
your memories will only return for as long
as you're in contact with the notebook.

141
00:08:32,137 --> 00:08:33,596
As soon as you let go of it,

142
00:08:33,722 --> 00:08:35,849
your memories will disappear again.

143
00:08:38,601 --> 00:08:42,188
[Light] That means I've gotta kill Higuchi
without letting go of this notebook.

144
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,815
If I manage to do that,

145
00:08:43,898 --> 00:08:47,027
ownership will transfer back to me
and my memories won't disappear.

146
00:08:47,277 --> 00:08:48,319
Hmm...

147
00:08:50,321 --> 00:08:53,241
I just have to pull this four times
in less than a second.

148
00:08:54,075 --> 00:08:55,035
Got it.

149
00:08:55,869 --> 00:08:57,454
Just as I expected:

150
00:08:57,579 --> 00:08:58,955
I'm wearing this watch.

151
00:08:59,164 --> 00:09:01,041
Old habits die hard.

152
00:09:02,167 --> 00:09:03,710
[loud heartbeat]

153
00:09:12,635 --> 00:09:15,430
Mr. Yagami,
please take Higuchi to the car.

154
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:18,975
[Yagami] Uh, right. Of course.

155
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:21,561
[loud heartbeat]

156
00:09:21,770 --> 00:09:22,771
KYOSUKE HIGUCHI

157
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:24,689
[panting]

158
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:29,235
-[Light] You know, about this notebook…
-Huh?

159
00:09:29,736 --> 00:09:33,073
[Light] I wonder what we would find
if we put it through forensic analysis.

160
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:35,075
[L] That doesn't sound like you,
Light.

161
00:09:35,158 --> 00:09:37,327
We both know this thing is beyond science.

162
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:38,787
[chuckles]

163
00:09:39,037 --> 00:09:41,372
Yeah, you're right. Hmm…

164
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:46,169
[footsteps echoing]

165
00:09:52,383 --> 00:09:56,262
This has gotta be
the longest 40 seconds of my life.

166
00:10:00,350 --> 00:10:03,436
[loud ticking]

167
00:10:07,315 --> 00:10:08,650
Ooh...

168
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:11,444
[Higuchi grunting]

169
00:10:12,695 --> 00:10:13,988
[Yagami] Higuchi.

170
00:10:14,072 --> 00:10:15,448
Ryuzaki, Higuchi is…

171
00:10:15,657 --> 00:10:17,283
What the hell?! What's happening?

172
00:10:19,911 --> 00:10:21,496
[Yagami] Hey, Higuchi!

173
00:10:22,247 --> 00:10:23,623
[Light] Dad, what are you doing?

174
00:10:23,706 --> 00:10:26,251
We can't lose him!
If Higuchi dies on us now--

175
00:10:26,501 --> 00:10:27,836
[Yagami] It's impossible!

176
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:30,922
The… but… [sighs]
There's nothing I can do.

177
00:10:31,172 --> 00:10:32,382
He's already…

178
00:10:34,384 --> 00:10:36,928
[Light] Yes. He's already dead.

179
00:10:37,679 --> 00:10:39,013
And you're next,

180
00:10:39,472 --> 00:10:40,515
Ryuzaki.

181
00:11:27,770 --> 00:11:29,189
[Aizawa] "How to use it."

182
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:33,526
It says, "The human whose name
is written in this notebook…

183
00:11:33,818 --> 00:11:34,986
shall die.

184
00:11:35,862 --> 00:11:37,405
"This note will not take effect

185
00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:39,824
unless the writer has the person's face
in their mind

186
00:11:39,949 --> 00:11:41,367
when writing his or her name.

187
00:11:41,451 --> 00:11:44,579
Therefore, people sharing the same name
will not be affected.

188
00:11:44,829 --> 00:11:45,747
[Light typing]

189
00:11:45,914 --> 00:11:49,542
[Aizawa] If the cause of death is written
40 seconds of writing the person’s name,

190
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:50,627
it will happen.

191
00:11:50,752 --> 00:11:52,879
If the cause of death is not specified,

192
00:11:53,004 --> 00:11:55,006
the person will simply die
of a heart attack.

193
00:11:57,175 --> 00:11:59,135
After writing the cause of death,

194
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:03,723
details of the death should be written
in the next six minutes and 40 seconds."

195
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:11,689
As well, the back cover has some more
instructions on how to use it.

196
00:12:12,273 --> 00:12:14,484
There are two more rules.
One of them is,

197
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:18,071
"If you make this note unusable
by tearing it up or burning it,

198
00:12:18,238 --> 00:12:20,198
all the humans
who have touched the note till then

199
00:12:20,365 --> 00:12:21,532
-will die."
-What?

200
00:12:21,616 --> 00:12:22,572
Is that really true, Aizawa?

201
00:12:22,648 --> 00:12:24,603
-[Aizawa] Yeah, that’s what it says.
-[Light] That's right.

202
00:12:24,697 --> 00:12:27,097
-[Matsuda] No way! That sucks!
-[Light] With a rule like that in place...

203
00:12:27,173 --> 00:12:28,960
-[Matsuda] Why didn't you tell me
before I touched it?

204
00:12:29,050 --> 00:12:31,621
-... the notebook's safety is guaranteed.
[Aizawa] How was I supposed to know?

205
00:12:31,707 --> 00:12:33,546
[Light] Which means my memories
of it will remain.

206
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:35,630
[Ryuk] Rem, there's no way
the old man back home

207
00:12:35,713 --> 00:12:36,673
will get mad at us

208
00:12:36,756 --> 00:12:38,549
if we write fake rules in here, is there?

209
00:12:38,675 --> 00:12:41,678
[Rem] No. There are no rules
against doing so.

210
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:43,513
Fine then, Light, I'll do it.

211
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:47,183
But you owe me an apple for this.
[cackles]

212
00:12:48,101 --> 00:12:49,560
Oh man, maybe I shouldn't have

213
00:12:49,644 --> 00:12:52,730
let my curiosity about seeing a Shinigami
get the better of me.

214
00:12:52,981 --> 00:12:55,566
Maybe, but then you would be
the only one in the investigation

215
00:12:55,650 --> 00:12:57,568
who didn't know what we were dealing with.

216
00:12:57,694 --> 00:12:58,861
Is that what you want?

217
00:12:58,945 --> 00:12:59,988
Uh, no, of course not.

218
00:13:00,071 --> 00:13:02,949
I wanna be on the same page
as everyone else on the Task Force, Chief.

219
00:13:04,158 --> 00:13:06,744
And then… [sighs] there's this last rule.

220
00:13:09,872 --> 00:13:13,001
According to these instructions
in the back of the notebook,

221
00:13:13,501 --> 00:13:15,295
"If the person using the note

222
00:13:15,378 --> 00:13:18,006
fails to consecutively write
names of people

223
00:13:18,172 --> 00:13:20,383
to be killed
within thirteen days of each other,

224
00:13:20,508 --> 00:13:22,760
then the user will die."

225
00:13:25,346 --> 00:13:27,056
[Matsuda gasps] Wait a second.

226
00:13:27,515 --> 00:13:28,433
If that's true,

227
00:13:28,558 --> 00:13:31,561
then it means Light and Misa-Misa
are completely clear, doesn't it?

228
00:13:31,644 --> 00:13:33,855
[Aizawa] Yeah, now that you mention it,
that's right.

229
00:13:33,938 --> 00:13:36,399
Light and Misa were detained
for more than 50 days

230
00:13:36,566 --> 00:13:37,942
and are still under surveillance.

231
00:13:38,026 --> 00:13:39,569
If either of them had been Kira,

232
00:13:39,694 --> 00:13:41,696
there's no way
they would still be alive by now.

233
00:13:41,779 --> 00:13:43,323
Wow, that’s great news, isn't it, Chief?

234
00:13:43,740 --> 00:13:44,782
[Yagami] Yeah.

235
00:13:45,867 --> 00:13:46,826
Rem, was it?

236
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:49,412
That's your name, isn't it?
The white thing over there?

237
00:13:49,746 --> 00:13:53,082
Ryuzaki, isn't it a bit rude to go around
calling someone a "white thing"?

238
00:13:53,166 --> 00:13:54,417
[Rem] What do you want?

239
00:13:54,751 --> 00:13:57,670
[L] There's more than one notebook
in the human world, isn't there?

240
00:14:00,089 --> 00:14:01,215
[Rem] Who knows.

241
00:14:01,382 --> 00:14:03,301
There may be and there may not be.

242
00:14:04,427 --> 00:14:07,347
If there are other notebooks either here
or in your world,

243
00:14:07,430 --> 00:14:09,515
would they all have the same rules
as this one?

244
00:14:09,849 --> 00:14:11,893
You're wasting your time, Ryuzaki.

245
00:14:11,976 --> 00:14:14,520
You'll never get Rem
to admit these rules are fake.

246
00:14:14,771 --> 00:14:16,773
[Rem] Yes, they are all the same.

247
00:14:17,148 --> 00:14:19,776
There are many notebooks
in the Shinigami Realm,

248
00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:21,569
but they all have the same rules.

249
00:14:21,819 --> 00:14:24,364
Even the rules
for when humans obtain them.

250
00:14:24,572 --> 00:14:25,823
Ryuzaki!

251
00:14:26,407 --> 00:14:28,910
[Aizawa] Misa Amane and Light have both
been cleared of suspicion.

252
00:14:29,118 --> 00:14:31,037
They shouldn’t be under surveillance
any longer.

253
00:14:31,287 --> 00:14:33,122
[Matsuda] That's right,
it's crystal clear!

254
00:14:35,917 --> 00:14:37,377
I suppose you're right…

255
00:14:48,096 --> 00:14:49,263
[L] I understand.

256
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:53,059
[L] Please, except my apologies
for all the trouble.

257
00:14:54,685 --> 00:14:55,770
[Matsuda and Aizawa sigh]

258
00:14:56,437 --> 00:14:57,814
Thank goodness.

259
00:14:58,022 --> 00:14:59,107
Yeah, but…

260
00:14:59,232 --> 00:15:02,568
We still can’t say we’ve solved the case
until we’ve figured out everything.

261
00:15:02,819 --> 00:15:03,861
Would it be all right

262
00:15:03,945 --> 00:15:06,697
if I kept investigating with you,
without the handcuffs on?

263
00:15:06,989 --> 00:15:07,990
Yes.

264
00:15:09,659 --> 00:15:13,329
[Light] And just like that,
Misa and I are proven innocent.

265
00:15:13,538 --> 00:15:17,417
A notebook of death filled with rules
written by a Shinigami.

266
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:19,877
He has no choice but to believe it.

267
00:15:20,545 --> 00:15:24,090
He just lost his edge
thanks to the fake rules I created.

268
00:15:25,258 --> 00:15:26,634
Listen Ryuzaki:

269
00:15:28,136 --> 00:15:31,806
no matter what the world,
the god of that world creates the rules.

270
00:15:31,889 --> 00:15:35,268
In truth, you've already been defeated
by the rules I created.

271
00:15:35,435 --> 00:15:38,521
And as punishment
for defying the god of the New World,

272
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:40,106
you will die.

273
00:15:44,652 --> 00:15:45,528
Oh, Light!

274
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:47,613
Be sure to text me every day, okay?

275
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:48,656
[Matsuda crying]

276
00:15:48,739 --> 00:15:51,200
[Matsuda] After all this time,
we're saying goodbye to Misa-Misa.

277
00:15:51,325 --> 00:15:53,953
Knock it off, Matsuda!
Let's leave them alone.

278
00:15:54,454 --> 00:15:55,580
[Matsuda] Goodbye Misa-Misa!

279
00:15:55,788 --> 00:15:56,873
[Aizawa] Enough!

280
00:16:00,042 --> 00:16:02,044
[Light] Good,
there are surveillance cameras,

281
00:16:02,128 --> 00:16:05,089
but they won't be able to pick out
my face or mouth at this angle.

282
00:16:05,965 --> 00:16:08,176
Misa, I'm gonna tell you
about a special place.

283
00:16:08,301 --> 00:16:10,178
I need you to go there
and dig something up,

284
00:16:10,261 --> 00:16:12,513
but you have to make sure
that no one is watching.

285
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:15,308
Light! Your memory must have returned!

286
00:16:15,850 --> 00:16:17,393
Don't worry, I can do this.

287
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:18,811
I won't let you down.

288
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:28,988
[gasps]

289
00:16:39,332 --> 00:16:40,541
[Misa] Light, I remember!

290
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:43,586
I remember everything that happened
when I had this notebook.

291
00:16:44,128 --> 00:16:45,379
You buried this one,

292
00:16:45,505 --> 00:16:48,049
so I could come here
and regain my memories.

293
00:16:49,592 --> 00:16:50,468
Huh?

294
00:16:50,628 --> 00:16:53,095
FOR MISA, LIGHT YAGAMI

295
00:16:53,471 --> 00:16:54,639
[Light's voice] "Dear Misa,

296
00:16:54,722 --> 00:16:57,975
by the time you read this letter,
you should've remembered everything."

297
00:16:59,477 --> 00:17:01,103
Oh, a letter from Light!

298
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:05,525
[Light] Do you remember
my friend at To-Oh University?

299
00:17:05,608 --> 00:17:07,527
He went by the name "Hideki Ryuga."

300
00:17:08,903 --> 00:17:11,280
I want you to write his real name
in the notebook

301
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:12,615
and kill him.

302
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:14,992
Then burn this letter right away.

303
00:17:15,910 --> 00:17:18,120
Take a number of pages from the notebook,

304
00:17:18,287 --> 00:17:20,122
and rebury it where you found it.

305
00:17:20,373 --> 00:17:22,208
The next time that we see each other,

306
00:17:22,333 --> 00:17:24,544
casually touch me
with a piece of the notebook.

307
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:27,046
If you do this for me,

308
00:17:27,505 --> 00:17:29,090
I promise I will love you...

309
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:31,968
-for the rest of my life.
-[Misa] …for the rest of my life! Yay!

310
00:17:32,343 --> 00:17:33,636
[Misa] Now I see.

311
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:35,596
This was all part of Light's plan!

312
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:39,225
He wanted me to get this notebook,
regain all my memories,

313
00:17:39,392 --> 00:17:41,894
and then kill Hideki Ryuga.

314
00:17:42,103 --> 00:17:43,563
Kill Ryuzaki.

315
00:17:44,438 --> 00:17:46,983
One of Light's biggest obstacles
will be gone,

316
00:17:47,066 --> 00:17:49,026
and I'll be helpful to him at last!

317
00:17:51,487 --> 00:17:53,990
Oh, but Light, it's no good!

318
00:17:55,074 --> 00:17:56,909
I don’t remember his name anymore!

319
00:17:57,868 --> 00:17:59,328
I was seeing dozens-- no,

320
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:02,540
no, no hundreds of names and lifespans
every day!

321
00:18:04,417 --> 00:18:07,295
Oh! I can't remember it no matter what!

322
00:18:07,545 --> 00:18:09,046
Oh, I'm such an idiot!

323
00:18:09,589 --> 00:18:10,673
[Misa] Huh?

324
00:18:12,008 --> 00:18:14,010
I finally return to the human world!

325
00:18:14,176 --> 00:18:15,428
Huh? Ryuk!

326
00:18:15,761 --> 00:18:18,347
[Misa] Oh, it's been so long!
Oh, I'm so glad to see you.

327
00:18:18,514 --> 00:18:20,433
-How are you doing?
-Sorry, uh.

328
00:18:21,309 --> 00:18:22,268
Ugh!

329
00:18:23,227 --> 00:18:25,855
I'm a guy, I get a little shy,
some… times.

330
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:27,064
[giggles]

331
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:28,983
[Misa] Oh yeah, I almost forgot.

332
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:30,067
Here!

333
00:18:30,693 --> 00:18:32,528
Light told me to bring one for you.

334
00:18:35,197 --> 00:18:36,741
Is it really that good?

335
00:18:36,824 --> 00:18:38,909
[Ryuk] Oh yeah. Human apples are--

336
00:18:38,993 --> 00:18:40,703
what's the word-- juicy, I think.

337
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:42,204
They're great, anyway.

338
00:18:44,332 --> 00:18:46,250
[mumbles] Why don't you try this?

339
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:47,418
Huh?

340
00:18:47,543 --> 00:18:50,254
[Ryuk gulps]
An apple from the Shinigami world.

341
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:53,299
Uhh… Ew, it doesn't look very good.

342
00:18:53,507 --> 00:18:55,051
Come on, one bite won't kill ya.

343
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:56,677
Mmm…

344
00:18:57,261 --> 00:18:58,846
By the way, before I forget,

345
00:18:59,055 --> 00:19:01,307
I want you to make the eye deal with me.

346
00:19:01,891 --> 00:19:03,309
[Misa biting apple]

347
00:19:05,102 --> 00:19:06,979
Peh! Peh! It's sand! Bleh.

348
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:08,522
Ugh!

349
00:19:12,693 --> 00:19:13,611
A deal, huh?

350
00:19:13,944 --> 00:19:15,196
Mmhmm.

351
00:19:16,030 --> 00:19:17,907
You understand what that means?

352
00:19:18,074 --> 00:19:20,993
You already made the same deal with Rem
once before.

353
00:19:21,494 --> 00:19:22,536
Are you sure

354
00:19:22,620 --> 00:19:24,664
you really want me
to cut your lifespan in half,

355
00:19:24,872 --> 00:19:26,248
for the second time?

356
00:19:26,415 --> 00:19:29,085
Uh... I know, but what choice do I have?

357
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:33,798
You see, I've forgotten a name
that I absolutely have to remember.

358
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:36,842
Light will be so mad at me
if I let him down.

359
00:19:38,386 --> 00:19:40,429
Heh, well it's fine with me.

360
00:19:47,436 --> 00:19:48,896
[Matsuda] Hey, it's Misa-Misa.

361
00:19:49,230 --> 00:19:50,147
The poor girl.

362
00:19:50,272 --> 00:19:52,692
As long as we're stuck in here,
we can't turn our cellphones on,

363
00:19:52,775 --> 00:19:55,778
so she has to come all the way out here
just to hang out with Light.

364
00:19:56,696 --> 00:19:58,781
Light, would you hurry up and go see her?

365
00:19:58,906 --> 00:20:01,367
Don't you know,
you should never keep a woman waiting.

366
00:20:02,201 --> 00:20:03,119
Okay.

367
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:06,997
Huh?

368
00:20:07,707 --> 00:20:08,749
Ryuk.

369
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:11,252
Why is he attached to Misa?

370
00:20:11,794 --> 00:20:12,712
Huh?

371
00:20:15,548 --> 00:20:16,966
[Rem] Misa's lifespan!

372
00:20:17,091 --> 00:20:18,551
It's been halved again!

373
00:20:18,926 --> 00:20:22,096
No! Did she make the eye deal with Ryuk?

374
00:20:24,974 --> 00:20:25,933
Hey, Light.

375
00:20:31,647 --> 00:20:33,023
It's been a while, Ryuk.

376
00:20:33,858 --> 00:20:36,360
[Ryuk cackles]

377
00:20:38,446 --> 00:20:40,072
Light, I'm so sorry!

378
00:20:40,156 --> 00:20:42,241
I don't remember Hideki Ryuga's real name!

379
00:20:42,366 --> 00:20:44,160
I tried, but I totally forgot!

380
00:20:44,493 --> 00:20:45,619
Oh, I see.

381
00:20:45,703 --> 00:20:47,037
Well, that's too bad.

382
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:50,249
But I did the eye deal with Ryuk,
so I can try again!

383
00:20:50,499 --> 00:20:52,585
So, everything's going according to plan…

384
00:20:52,793 --> 00:20:53,669
You idiot!

385
00:20:53,836 --> 00:20:55,546
If you do that,
then your lifespan will--

386
00:20:55,629 --> 00:20:57,047
Mmm… no, it's all right.

387
00:20:57,131 --> 00:20:59,008
I just want to be of use to you, Light.

388
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:05,556
Misa, all I want is

389
00:21:05,681 --> 00:21:08,476
to enjoy a long life with you
in an ideal world.

390
00:21:08,893 --> 00:21:10,102
That's how I feel.

391
00:21:10,519 --> 00:21:11,812
Light, I'm so happy.

392
00:21:12,855 --> 00:21:14,774
[Light] Let's create a New World together.

393
00:21:15,149 --> 00:21:18,569
It'll be a place with no crime,
where only kind people live.

394
00:21:18,736 --> 00:21:20,196
-Okay?
-[Misa] Yeah.

395
00:21:29,865 --> 00:21:35,336
TO BE CONTINUED

396
00:21:53,189 --> 00:21:55,272
[theme song playing]
